## Specific source issue that caused the persistent failure

The source line:

```markdown
The TFSSP has evolved over time. In September 2019, Change 9 of the TFSSP became effective. Since 2019, TSA has issued nine (9) additional program changes, including technical amendments. These program changes included, but were not limited to, adding training requirements for insider threat awareness, establishing cybersecurity incident reporting requirements, establishing a cybersecurity coordinator, and developing an aircraft operator ID Media Plan. In addition to these changes, TSA is issuing a program re-write {==(Change 17) ==}{>>Pitino, Salvatore (2025-07-25): ACD: EAB is using ‘Change 17’ as a placeholder based on Change 16 issued by PPE Aviation in Jan. 2025.<<}which introduces new requirements for twelve-five operators and modifies other requirements currently in place. These requirements include, but are not limited to, the incorporation of cargo screening requirements with technology, Standard Security Screening Procedures for Air Cargo (SSPAC), Security Threat Assessment (STA) requirements, Known Shipper Management System (KSMS) requirements, and Cargo Acceptance and Transfer Measures.
```

Validator observed model underlying output as:

```markdown
... TSA is issuing a program re-write (Change 17) which introduces ...
```

But expected raw source as:

```markdown
... TSA is issuing a program re-write {==(Change 17) ==}{>>Pitino, Salvatore ...<<}which introduces ...
```

That proves the validator is stripping or interpreting source CriticMarkup from the response.

