## Bottom line

The model is not the primary blocker at this point. The persistent offset `13608` failure is caused by the downstream validator interpreting pre-existing CriticMarkup in the source as if it were new model markup. The most robust fix is to sentinelize pre-existing CriticMarkup before prompting and validation, then restore it after validation.
